article.headline: Navy 76, Lafayette 57
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. (AP) -- Senior Taj Mathews celebrated his final home game by scoring 24 points to lead Navy over Lafayette, 76-57, on Wednesday. Classmate George O'Garro also stood out on Senior Night, recording 10 points and 11 rebounds for the Midshipmen, who clinched the No. 6 seed for the Patriot League Tournament. David Hooper added 12 points for Navy (9-17, 5-8), which equaled school and Patriot League records for total rebounds (71) and rebounding margin (plus-38). Navy also set a school record for rebounding margin (71-33). Matt Fannin grabbed a team-high 14 rebounds for the Midshipmen, who had more offensive boards (36) than defensive (35). Bilal Abdullah scored 14 points for Lafayette (8-18, 4-9), which will be seeded seventh for the postseason tournament that begins March 4. Mathews made four 3-pointers in the opening five minutes as Navy raced out to a 16-6 lead. Marcus Harley scored all 10 of his points in the first half for the Leopards, who rallied to take their only lead at 26-24 and trailed 38-34 at intermission. Navy outscored Lafayette 11-4 to open the second half, opening a 49-38 lead that the Midshipmen steadily pushed higher.
